Introduction
============
SmartRunner simplifies the creation and execution of tests for mobile devices. The tool enable you to use the features of products for developing, debugging, deploying, running, and monitoring tests.

smartrunner setup
=================
environment
-----------
* ubuntu: 10.04. 11.04. 12.04. English version 32 bit or 64 bit
* python: 2.7.x
* python library: python-opencv. python-numpy
* adb,sdb work on your machine

depend library installation:
sudo apt-get install python-opencv	
sudo apt-get install python-numpy

usage	
-----
1: push EasyAutomator.jar to device
UIAutomator is only available on devices with API level 16 or higher (Android 4.1 and 4.2). And some API only available on API level 17. it's not be available on a 2.3.3 device.

Run the following command on a command-line to get the version of Android installed:
adb shell getprop ro.build.version.sdk

For Android device with API 16 or higher, please push EasyAutomator.jar to device via adb:
adb push EasyAutomator.jar /mnt/sdcard/

2: demo script:
python runtest.py --plan android_sample/plan/plan --product android_sample

      
